Read IR-finderS output

Source: R/ir_realted.R
read_irfinderS_output.Rd

Read IR-finderS output

Usage

read_irfinderS_output(files, add_prefix_chr = TRUE, remove_prefix_chr = FALSE)

Arguments

files

a character vector denoting irfinderS output file(s) ending with suffix "IR-nondir".

add_prefix_chr

logical, whether to add prefix 'chr' in the column seq names

remove_prefix_chr

logical, whether to remove prefix 'chr' from the column seq names

select_columns

logical, whether to subset columns. If TRUE below columns will be subsetted

  • chr

  • start

  • end

  • name

  • null

  • strand

  • coverage

  • introndepth

  • spliceleft

  • spliceright

  • spliceexact

  • irratio

  • warnings

Value

Examples

example_dir <- system.file("extdata" ,"ir_data" , package="parcutils")
example_files <- fs::dir_ls(example_dir, glob = "*-IR-nondir*.txt")
names(example_files) <- stringr::str_replace(example_files , pattern = ".*/", replacement = "") %>%
stringr::str_replace(pattern = "-IR-nondir.txt", replacement = "")
read_irfinderS_output(files = example_files,  add_prefix_chr = F)
